<p>This tab shows statistics for all sent messages or those messages sent to one specific list.</p><p> The administrator permissions for the clickstats/mviews page control whether the current user may see all messages, only those messages of which he is the owner, or does not have access to the plugin.</p>When all sent messages are shown then all users who received the message are included.When a message sent to one list is shown, then only users who belong to that list are included.</p><p>The sent, opened, clicked and bounced figures do not include test messages sent when preparing a message.</p><table><tr><td>Heading</td><td>This shows the list or lists to which the messages have been sent.</td></tr><tr><td>Download</td><td>The fields displayed can be downloaded as a CSV file.</td></tr><tr><td>Graph</td><td>The graph is a bar chart showing the number of users who were sent each message as columns, with overlays of the number of users who opened, clicked a link, or bounced.</td></tr><tr><td>ID&nbsp;|&nbsp;Subject </td><td>The message number and subject of the message. This is a link to the Opened tab.</td></tr><tr><td>Date</td><td>The date when the message was last sent.</td></tr><tr><td>Sent</td><td>The number of users to which the message was sent.</td></tr><tr><td>Opened</td><td>The % (total) of users who have opened the message.</td></tr><tr><td>Clicked</td><td>This shows three figures separated by | <ol><li>the % (total) users who have clicked at least one link in the message<li>the total number of clicks of all links<li>the users clicked / users opened %</ol></td></tr><tr><td>Bounced</td><td>The % (total) of bounced email addresses.</td></tr><tr><td>Views</td><td>The number of times (average per user) that the message has been viewed.This is the same value as the 'viewed' figure on the Messages page.Note that this includes all users who were sent the message, so may be incorrect when a message has been sent to more than one list. This figure does include views of a test message. </td></tr></table>